Priority 1:
    -AI
        Write a c++ program to calculate the ground state of the Dirac hydrogen atom.  Details:
        1) Hint: These specifications are based on refining two previous AI attempts at this problem,
           contained in my files UnitTests/HydrogenAI.C UnitTests/HydrogenAI2.C
        2) Use an RKB (Restricted Kinetic Balance) Gaussian basis set. 
        3) Use an even tempered set of exponents: alpha*beta^i, i=0...N-1.  With alpha=0.01, beta=2, N=22
        4) Hint: Cholsky decomposition of the overlap matrix, and triangular inversion might be the most numericlly stable way to
            orthogonalize the resulting generalized eigen system.
        5) Use blaze library calls for any linear algebra and matrix classes. 
        6) Hint: Make sure the Hamiltonian is symmetric (real hermitian). As such there should be no need to check complex eigen values. 
        7) Include a rest mass term -mc2 in Hamiltonian so that electron state eigen values are comparable
           with non-relatavistic eigen values
        8) Throw out all positron eigen solutions (eigen values < -mc2) so we can focus on the electron
           solutions only.
        9) Hint use c_light variable name for the speed of light in a.u. (in case the name c gets used somewhere else)
        10) Also do a total energy calculation using the *eletron* ground state eigen vector, using kinetic and potential operator expectation values.
        11) compare electron ground state eigen value and total energy with reference enrgy -0.50000665 a.u.

